                    h1 Bearly Awake almost ready for winter hibernation
                    small presented by Ringle Bingle: first you Ringle, then you Bingle!                    
                    p
                        | Sitting at 1-5 and with a matchup against Trashman Industries (5-1), Bearly Awake stays true to its namesake. Brendan Haggerty, a notorious napper and ex-Sleeper, appears to be preparing for a long winter hibernation with playoff odds of just 2%.
                    p
                        | Bearly Awake has taken a near perfect bee line to hibernation from the start of the season. Their only win comes Week 1 as he was unable to out sleep his ex-teamate and former Sleeper, Brian Feldman of Long S. Napper.

                    p
                        | As the name suggests, Brandon Haggerty is bearly awake. "I wouldn't count him out" says a representative from Trashman Industires. After this week, their remaining schedule includes teams at or below 500.
                    
                    h3 Early-Week Waiver Report
                    p
                        | Week 7 was yet another busy week with a total of 11 successful claims, tied for third busiest waiver day thus far. Womb Goof spent a total of $91 on the eve of good news about Ezekiel Elliots' suspension. A strange move given the good news and lack of need for 2 RBs and a WR. Some speculate that he may have been so excited that he forgot to cancel his waiver claims. Gillislegally Brown had the most efficient claim, beating out ISC by $1 for Chris Ivory.
                    h3 Early-Week Matchup Preview
                    p
                        | One of the more interesting matchups to keep an eye on this week is Womb Goof at Brooklyn Dodgers. Womb Goof owner Stephen London has never beaten Brooklyn Dodgers owner Greg McGinniss.
                    p
                        | At the halfway mark of the season, Crow-lin Powell and Caffreine Free will try to keep their playoff hopes alive in what may prove to be a pivotal game for both teams. A loss for Caffreine Free will bring him nearly to the brink.
