                    h2 Trashman Industires Blockade of Gillislegally Brown uncovered
                    p
                        | The Trash Zone obtained a confidential memo on Thursday highlighting a Trashman Industries directive to block Gillislegally Brown. Anonymous sources claim there's much more to the program and that Trashman Industries has an "extensive program of hybrid warfare" directed at Gillislegally Brown.
                    p
                        | Gillislegally Brown has a matchup this week with Sarah London's Disapproval whose trade with Trashman Industries was part of a "Blockade program." At the time of the trade, Trashman Industries was advised against the trade by a close ally. The trade appears to have strained that relationship. The ally, who wishes to remain anonymous, pleaded with the Trashman to "force them to stream" and warned him that this trade "may be your undoing in the playoffs." In light of this confidential memo, the trade appears to have furthered Trashman Industries interests on many fronts and was not simply about improving their roster. Although, it is too early to tell whether or not this trade and program will be effective.
                    p
                        | We have been unable to confirm many of the claims put forth by our source and Trashman Industries declined to comment on the report saying that they do not comment on classified material.
